cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a convolutional neural network (CNN) based algorithm for automatic body part recognition in CT slices. The paper also mentions two applications of the proposed algorithm in network initialization and anomaly detection, which are common tasks in computer vision. 

The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of deep learning methods further supports this possibility. 

The paper's focus on medical image applications and the use of CT volumes suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper's use of inter-slice relationships and spatial ordering information could also suggest that it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's use of a self-organization process in the training of the algorithm could suggest that it belongs to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
